        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "With `BufRead` it would just shift the problem somewhere else and not in a good way, so I don't think it should be done.\n\nBut moving to buffer variables and getting rid of `BufWipeout` seems natural and it's not just shifting the problem. Unless there is a reason not to keep potentially a lot of data in buffer variables. We can avoid iterating over all of the buffers if we keep a list of just buffer ids where diagnostics have been set and cleaning it up when getting diagnostics for all buffers if it turns out some of those buffers don't exist anymore.",
