        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Ok. It looks like the `BufWipeout` handler is trying to cleanup a cache. It's a bit strange that it only handles `BufWipeout`, since that is usually not how buffers are deleted, which means the cache rarely gets cleaned up...\n\nIt definitely would make sense to store data on buffers instead of maintaining a parallel cache. That's generally a best practice, it avoids the need for these \"cleanup\" handlers entirely.",
