        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk the only thing to keep in mind is that storing the cache in buffer variables makes it completely public. Meaning it could be directly manipulated from outside of core. Currently it's public to read via `vim.diagnostic.get`, but it makes a `deepcopy`, so external modifications do not affect it:\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/d7164eced6d6dc363eaee0c47538c5ff6552e3ba/runtime/lua/vim/diagnostic/_store.lua#L294\n\nI assume there was a reason to not let it be directly modified. With buffer variables I don't think there is any way to achieve that.",
